@michaelsembwever , I think @eddumelendez  makes a good point. 
Existing [CassandraAutoConfiguration](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/api/org/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/cassandra/CassandraAutoConfiguration.html) provides the basics to setup connection. It also provides extensive list of [CassandraProperties](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/api/org/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/cassandra/CassandraProperties.html). 
For example you can check The PGVector (relying on JdbcTemplateAutoConfiguration), Neo4jVectorStoreAutoConfiguration on Neo4jAutoConfiguration, ElasticsearchVectorStoreAutoConfiguration on ElasticsearchRestClientAutoConfiguration and maybe more.
